 done and good to go whenever it needs to branch (including work that doesn’t involve evolution proposals, like improved compile time, better error messages, etc). <br></p><p>Overall, we’re not managing a specific feature set goal for it, we’re just treating it as an incremental step along the way to Swift 4.<br></p><p>-Chris<br></p><p>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20161011/b24ff3cb/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
